# Client Hook Conventions

## Hook Structure

Each feature has a `use-{feature}.ts` hook that manages:
- State (`entries`, `isAdmin`, `isLoading`, `ownedIds`)
- CRUD operations (`createEntry`, `updateEntry`, `deleteEntry`)
- Ownership checks (`isOwned`, `canDelete`, `canEdit`)

## Pattern

```typescript
export function useFeature(options: { initialEntries?: Entry[]; initialIsAdmin?: boolean; currentUserId?: string } = {}) {
  const [entries, setEntries] = useState(options.initialEntries ?? []);
  const [isAdmin, setIsAdmin] = useState(options.initialIsAdmin ?? false);
  const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(!options.initialEntries);

  // Fetch if no SSR data provided
  useEffect(() => { if (!options.initialEntries) loadEntries(); }, [options.initialEntries]);

  // CRUD with useCallback, optimistic deletes
  const createEntry = useCallback(async (input) => {
    const res = await fetch("/api/feature", { method: "POST", ... });
    const data = await res.json();
    setEntries(prev => [data.entry, ...prev]);
    if (data.newBadges?.length) emitBadgesEarned(data.newBadges);
    return data.entry;
  }, []);

  const deleteEntry = useCallback(async (id) => {
    const prev = entries;
    setEntries(e => e.filter(x => x.id !== id)); // optimistic
    const res = await fetch(`/api/feature?id=${id}`, { method: "DELETE" });
    if (!res.ok) setEntries(prev); // rollback
  }, [entries]);

  return { entries, isAdmin, isLoading, createEntry, updateEntry, deleteEntry, isOwned, canDelete };
}
```

## Key Conventions
- Accept `initialEntries` from SSR to avoid client-side refetch
- Use `useCallback` for all CRUD functions
- Optimistic delete: remove from state immediately, restore on failure
- Token-based ownership (guestbook, puzzles): check via `*-ownership.ts` lib (localStorage)
- Auth-based ownership (blog, loons, gallery): check `entry.user?.id === currentUserId`
- Always emit badges: `emitBadgesEarned(data.newBadges)` after create/update
